        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agent): add configurable timeout for query_agent calls",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add an opt-in `VOX_AGENT_TIMEOUT_MS` for HTTP and subprocess `query_agent` calls\n- keep existing installs upgrade-safe: unset or `0` leaves agent queries unbounded\n- use per-query HTTP abort controllers so one timeout does not poison later calls\n- send a generic model-visible failure while retaining detailed errors in server-side logs\n- request a follow-up Realtime response so calls recover instead of hanging\n- reject late HTTP queries after the agent client has closed\n\n## Runtime proof\n\nRan the built branch CLI through the real `vox serve` WebSocket path with a fake Realtime server, a Twilio-shaped caller socket, and a subprocess agent that never replies:\n\n```json\n{\"elapsedMs\":159,\"modelOutput\":{\"ok\":false,\"error\":\"Agent request failed\"},\"responseCreate\":true,\"loggedError\":\"Agent query timed out after 150ms\"}\n```\n\nThis proves the configured timeout fires, the caller/model receives no raw backend detail, `response.create` resumes the conversation, and diagnostics remain available in `events.jsonl`.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm run lint`\n- `pnpm run typecheck`\n- `pnpm test` (56 passed)\n- `pnpm run build`\n- focused stalled-agent, HTTP recovery, disabled-timeout, sanitization, and post-close regression tests\n- final Codex autoreview: no actionable findings\n",
